Create an issue for the Code Agent to fix.

<VERIFICATION_RESULT>
- Task: {{ task_id }}
- Passed: {{ 'YES' if passed else 'NO' }}
</VERIFICATION_RESULT>

<FAILED_CHECKS>
{% for check in failed_checks %}
- {{ check }}
{% endfor %}
</FAILED_CHECKS>

<PROBLEMS_FOUND>
{% for problem in problems %}
- {{ problem }}
{% endfor %}
</PROBLEMS_FOUND>

{% if error_logs %}
<ERROR_LOGS>
{{ error_logs }}
</ERROR_LOGS>
{% endif %}

{% if related_files %}
<RELATED_FILES>
{% for file in related_files %}
- {{ file }}
{% endfor %}
</RELATED_FILES>
{% endif %}

<INSTRUCTIONS>
Create a clear, actionable issue that the Code Agent can fix.
Include:
1. A concise title
2. Detailed description of what's wrong
3. The specific error message (if any)
4. Which file(s) need to be fixed
5. Suggested fix approach
6. How to verify the fix worked
</INSTRUCTIONS>

Respond in JSON:
```json
{
  "id": "issue_001",
  "task_id": "{{ task_id }}",
  "severity": "error|warning|suggestion",
  "title": "Brief issue title",
  "description": "Detailed description of the problem",
  "error_message": "Actual error message if any",
  "file_path": "path/to/problem/file",
  "line_number": null,
  "code_snippet": "relevant code if applicable",
  "suggested_fix": "How to fix this issue",
  "related_files": ["other", "files", "to", "check"],
  "verification_command": "command to verify fix",
  "expected_result": "what success looks like"
}
```

